    {
      "slug": "baked-soda-bath",
      "term": "Baked soda bath",
      "definition": "A water bath made with bicarbonate of soda (baking soda) used as a home-kitchen substitute for the food-grade lye used in professional pretzel baking. Poaching shaped rolls in the alkaline solution for 30 seconds per side gelatinises the surface starch, producing the characteristic dark gloss and chewy crust without handling caustic chemicals."
    }
  ],
