        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mix, knead, and bulk ferment, 1 hour"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combine {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{salt-table}}, and {{caster-sugar}}. Add the {{water}} and {{unsalted-butter}}. Bring together and knead for 10 minutes — the dough should be smooth, firm, and not sticky. Cover and leave until doubled, about 1 hour."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shape and prove, 30 minutes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Divide the dough into 8 equal pieces. Shape each into a tight round ball, pulling the surface taut. Place on an oiled baking tray, cover, and prove for 30 minutes until slightly puffed. Heat the oven to 210°C (190°C fan)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Poach and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bring the bath {{water}} to a rolling boil in a wide, deep pan. Add the {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} — it will foam briefly. Drop the rolls in 2 or 3 at a time and poach for 30 seconds per side. Lift out with a slotted spoon, drain briefly, and return to the oiled tray. Score a cross in the top of each roll with a sharp knife. Scatter {{sea-salt-flakes}} over the top. Bake for 18–20 minutes until deep brown. Cool on a wire rack for at least 10 minutes before cutting."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}